The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Punters Corner - Celestial fancied on Day I
                                                                          Friday , November 6 , 2009                                                                                                                                                                                            Celestial fancied on Day I 
            SRIMAX                            
	Bangalore: The 34-day Bangalore winter season is scheduled to start from Friday. A total stake money of Rs 8,91,24,375 is up for the grabs during the season which may see as many as 1,015 horses, including 375 two-year-olds, out to contest. Trainers S. Ganapathy, who had a lean summer season, and S. Padmanabhan are expected to dominate the season.           
	The following are the important events: The Bangalore 1,000 Guineas is on November 28, the 2000 Guineas on December 12), the Oaks is on January 2, 2010 and the Derby will be held on January 26.          
	The opening day may see, Padmanabhans Celestial Way (Suraj Narredu-up) winning the Rajyotsava Trophy, the main event.           
